Gnews :: Freedom

At a recent Google Cloud Next conference

  • Linux Foundation executive director Jim Zemlin said:
  • business models are changing to include open source
  • organizations that "don't harvest the shared innovation" of open source "will fail."

Message For AMD: Open PSP Will Improve Security, Hinder Intel

  • AMD has faced calls from Edward Snowden, Libreboot and the Reddit community to release the source code to the AMD Secure Processor (PSP), a network-capable co-processor which some believe has the capacity to act as a backdoor.
  • Opening the PSP would have security benefits, and would provide AMD with a competitive advantage against rival chipmaker Intel.
  • "Thanks for the feedback. Please believe me that this has CEO level attention and AMD is investigating the steps and resources necessary to support this. It is not the work of a minute, so please bear with us as we define what we can do."

me_cleaner : Intel Management Engine partial removal tool

  • ME firmware can be partially removed with this tool by writing 0xff over parts of the firmware so that it cannot be decompressed correctly.
  • Hashes are computed but bad hashes of some components are not considered critical to the operation of the system, and so are ignored.
  • me_cleaner on github

Open Source Car-Hacking Tool Successfully Crowdfunded

  • Two geeks are crowdfunding an open source car hacking tool that will allow builders to experiment with diagnostics, telematics, security, and prototyping.
  • "Cars have become complicated and expensive to work with,"
  • "Macchina wants to use open source hardware to help break down these barriers and get people tinkering with their cars again."
